    • Method Detail

      • isSourcePathOverlapAllowed

        boolean isSourcePathOverlapAllowed()
        Returns whether some source path directories are allowed to be subdirectories of another.
        Returns:
        true if source path overlap is allowed, false otherwise.

      • showActionScriptWarnings

        boolean showActionScriptWarnings()
        Returns whether ActionScript warnings are enabled. If enabled, the ActionScript compiler runs in a mode that detects legal but potentially incorrect code.
        Returns:
        true if ActionScript warnings are enabled, false otherwise.

      • showBindingWarnings

        boolean showBindingWarnings()
        Returns whether binding warnings are enabled. If binding warning are enabled, then warnings generated from data binding code are displayed.
        Returns:
        true if binding warnings are enabled, false otherwise.

      • showDeprecationWarnings

        boolean showDeprecationWarnings()
        Returns whether deprecation warnings are enabled. If deprecation warning are enabled, then warnings generated from the use of deprecated APIs are displayed.
        Returns:
        true if deprecation warnings are enabled, false otherwise.

      • showUnusedTypeSelectorWarnings

        boolean showUnusedTypeSelectorWarnings()
        Returns whether unused type selector warnings are enabled. If unused type selector warnings are enabled, then warnings generated from unused type selectors are displayed.
        Returns:
        true if unused type selector warnings are enabled, false otherwise.

      • showMultipleDefinitionWarnings

        boolean showMultipleDefinitionWarnings()
        Returns whether multiple definition warnings are enabled.
        Returns:
        true if multiple definition warnings are enabled, false otherwise.

      • isStrict

        boolean isStrict()
        Returns true if the compiler should run in strict error checking mode. In strict mode the compiler reports undefined property and function calls. The compiler also performs type checking on assignments and options supplied to method calls.
        Returns:
        true if strict error check mode is enabled, false otherwise.

      • getErrorProblems

        Collection<Class<ICompilerProblem>> getErrorProblems()
        A collection of problem classes that should be report as errors. This list overrides the default settings.
        Returns:
        collection of classes that should be reported as errors.

      • getWarningProblems

        Collection<Class<ICompilerProblem>> getWarningProblems()
        A collection of problem classes that should be report as warnings. This list overrides the default settings.
        Returns:
        collection of classes that should be reported as warnings.

      • getIgnoreProblems

        Collection<Class<ICompilerProblem>> getIgnoreProblems()
        A collection of problem classes that should not be reported. This list overrides the default settings.
        Returns:
        collection of classes that should be ignored.

        Returns whether checking of a type ActionScript warning is enabled. The kinds of warnings are:

 --compiler.warn-assignment-within-conditional
 --compiler.warn-bad-array-cast
 --compiler.warn-bad-bool-assignment
 --compiler.warn-bad-date-cast
 --compiler.warn-bad-es3-type-method

 --compiler.warn-boolean-constructor-with-no-args

 --compiler.warn-constructor-returns-value
 --compiler.warn-deprecated-event-handler-error

 --compiler.warn-duplicate-argument-names

 --compiler.warn-no-constructor
 --compiler.warn-no-explicit-super-call-in-constructor
 --compiler.warn-no-type-decl
 --compiler.warn-number-from-string-changes
 --compiler.warn-scoping-change-in-this
 --compiler.warn-slow-text-field-addition
 --compiler.warn-unlikely-function-value
 --compiler.warn-xml-class-has-changed

      • showWarnings

        boolean showWarnings()
        Determines if any warnings are shown. This is the master warning flag that overrides all other warning options.
        Returns:
        true if warnings should be shown, false otherwise.
